# CHANGELOG

This file lists all the updates made to our simple Math Calculator Project.

## Version v1.7.1 - February 10, 2025
- Resolved a bug when the calculation history received an error when no calculations were made by the user in the program.

--

## Version v1.7.0 - February 7, 2025
- Added feature for users to view their calculation history.

- - -

## Version v1.6.0 - November 16, 2025
- Added the logarithmic operation with the Python Math Library.

- - -

## Version v1.5.0 - October 23, 2025
- Added the exponent operation.

- - -

## Version v1.4.1 - September 21, 2025
- Resolved a bug when non-positive integers were determined to be composite or prime.

- - -

## Version v1.4.0 - September 16, 2025
- Added feature to determine whether a number is odd or even.
- Added feature to determine whether a number is prime or composite.

– - -

## Version v1.3.0 - August 30, 2025
– Added feature to divide two numbers. 

– - -

## Version v1.2.0 - August 25, 2025
– Added feature to multiply two numbers.

— - - 

## Version v1.1.1 - August 23, 2025
– Corrected grammar and wording in output messages and prompts.

– - -

## Version v1.1.0 - August 17, 2025
– Added feature so that the user can:
Choose to find the difference of two real numbers
Enter more than two real numbers for adding

– - -

## Version v1.0.0 - August 15, 2025
– First version of the Program
– User can:
Enter two real numbers
Calculate and display its sum
